After racing for 12 long days through the desert and covering over 7,500km, Sam Sunderland secured his third career podium at the Dakar with an admirable top-three result.

Matthias Walkner finished inside the top 10 despite an early setback, and rally rookie Daniel Sanders impressed the entire paddock with his fourth place result.

node.text:
@mxgp | Herlings to attempt Belgian Grand Prix

Jeffrey Herlings will wheel his Red Bull KTM 450 SX-F into the Lommel sand for the sixth round of 2021 MXGP tomorrow. The Dutchman fractured his left shoulder blade less than two weeks ago at the Dutch round of the series but has made progress and took to the practice track on Saturday morning to evaluate his condition. 

“I rode the bike today, and we’ll give it a go tomorrow,” he said. “It’s still a bit sore. I’m 50 points down in the championship at the moment so tomorrow will be about damage control. We’ll have four weeks to fully heal-up before going to Turkey. We’ll just do our best and focus on the second part of the races to keep going and get some points. Lommel is a track that suits me and I want to give it a shot at least; then I don’t have any regrets for the rest of the championship.”

#ReadyToRace #KTM #MXGP #MXGPBelgium @jeffrey_herlings84

Manuel Lettenbichler has finished as runner-up on Offroad Day 1 at Red Bull Romaniacs. 

Building his speed throughout the day, Mani got his head down when the going got tough to finish just three and a half minutes down on the leader after close to five hours of racing.

FMF KTM Factory Racing's Trystan Hart finished 11th on his first ever full day at Romaniacs.

With tomorrow marking the first half of the event's marathon stage, a gruelling two days of riding await all competitors at the world's toughest hard enduro rallye!

Winner of the two previous rounds of Red Bull Romaniacs, Manuel Lettenbichler will be looking to make it three-in-a-row this year as round four of the FIM Hard Enduro World Championship kicks off tomorrow.

Five days of racing await the riders, starting with a time trial qualification, followed by four full days of hard enduro action in the Carpathain Mountains. Mani faces a night under the stars after offroad day two with organisers introducing a marathon stage for the first time.

Marvin Musquin returns to form in Washougal to take his first moto podium of the season!

Third in race one, the KTM 450 SX-F FACTORY EDITION rider claimed fifth in race two for fourth overall.

Cooper Webb also showed good pace on the Washington track at round seven of the Pro Motocross Championship to go 7-6 for sixth overall.

In the 250MX class, Maximus Vohland delivered consistent results in both motos for an overall top-10 finish.
